      right: ["Severe intractable headache unresponsive to conservative measures and analgesics","Sudden change in level of consciousness or new focal neurological deficits (possible subdural hematoma)","New-onset diplopia or visual changes (cranial nerve VI palsy from brain herniation)","Signs of cerebral venous thrombosis (seizures, progressive headache, papilledema)","Rapidly progressive hearing loss (CN VIII compromise from brain sagging)","Signs of tonsillar herniation (occipital headache, neck rigidity, bradycardia, respiratory irregularity)"]
